Scores of persons have been burnt dead at Abacheke Kpofire illegal bunkering/refining site at the oil-bearing Egbema community of Ohaji/Egbema Local Government Area of Imo State. The persons numbering more than hundreds died as a result of the fire outbreak from the illegal refining site. The incident which occurred on Friday night puts the casualty figure at around more than 100. The Egbema youth president, Mr Okenya Theadus Mario confirmed the incident to Tribune Online in Owerri Saturday. He said that he has visited the scene where he discovered that an uncountable number of persons were burnt beyond recognition. He said some of the burnt corpses have even been buried.  The Imo State Police Command Public Relations Officer CSP Michael Abatham also confirmed the incident and described it as unfortunate. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE We Have Not Had Water Supply In Months ― Abeokuta Residents In spite of the huge investment in the water sector by the government and international organisations, water scarcity has grown to become a perennial nightmare for residents of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. This report x-rays the lives and experiences of residents in getting clean, potable and affordable water amidst the surge of COVID-19 cases in the state…Scores of persons burnt  Scores of persons burnt Selfies, video calls and Chinese documentaries: The things you’ll meet onboard Lagos-Ibadan train The Lagos-Ibadan railway was inaugurated recently for a full paid operation by the Nigerian Railway Corporation after about a year of free test-run. Our reporter joined the train to and fro Lagos from Ibadan and tells his experience in this report…Scores of persons burnt  Scores of persons burnt